Watch on youtube: https://youtu.be/TUKXkWP24ek Tags: 3dprint , addnorth , petg , material test , I tested two PETG filaments from AddNorth: Rigid X and regular PETG. Rigid X stands out as the stiffest PETG filament I've ever worked with, offering properties similar to ABS, including impressive temperature resistance. It's a fantastic alternative for those without an enclosed 3D printer who still want durable, high-performance prints.
